    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the CFD hemolysis model meets the minimum threshold for regulatory submission despite identified factor gaps. All 13 credibility factors were reviewed; 7 were formally assessed and 6 remain as epistemic gaps. The team concluded that the pressure-head and velocity-field validation results, combined with the bench hemolysis comparisons, provide sufficient evidence to support the VAD use claim. Uncertainty quantification activities are deferred to a subsequent assessment cycle.",
